abstract: Nissan says it will assist in opening about 1,000 high-speed charging stations for electric vehicles.
lead_paragraph: The move by Nissan comes days after BMW and Volkswagen announced a joint effort to build 100 high-speed public charging stations on the East and West Coasts.
snippet: The move by Nissan comes days after BMW and Volkswagen announced a joint effort to build 100 high-speed public charging stations on the East and West Coasts.

headline.main: Nissan Plans 1,000 New Stations to Quickly Charge Electric Cars
